Code Quality Rules:

1. Write production-ready code.
2. No placeholder code.
3. No TODO comments.
4. No mock implementations unless requested.
5. Follow ESLint rules.
6. Use meaningful naming.
7. Keep components under 250 lines.
8. Extract reusable hooks.
9. Use custom hooks for business logic.
10. Add proper TypeScript types.
